{"title_page": "Ziy\u0101d al-A\u02bfd\u0332j\u0332am", "text_new": "'''Ziy\u0101d al-A\u02bfd\u0332j\u0332am''' was an [[Arabic language|Arabic]] poet of the [[Umayyad Dynasty|Umayyad period]]. Of [[Persian people|Persian]]<ref name=\"eol\" /> origin, he was a [[mawla]] of the Amir b. al-Harith, a branch of the [[Abd al-Qays|Abd al-Kays]]. Ziy\u0101d owed his nickname, \"al-A\u02bfd\u0332j\u0332am,\" to his strong Persian accent. According to anecdotes told in the ''[[Aghani]]'', his grammar and pronunciation of spoken Arabic was not ideal.<ref name=\"eol\">{{cite book|last1=Pellat|first1=prepared by a number of leading orientalists ; edited by ... H.A.R. Gibb, J.H. Kramers, E. L\u00e9vi-Proven\u00e7al, J. Schacht, ... B. Lewis, Ch.|title=The encyclopaedia of Islam|date=1960|publisher=E.J. Brill|location=Leiden|isbn=9004127569|page=522|edition=New|quote=Of Persian origin, he was a mawla of the Amir b. al-Harith, a branch of the Abd al-Kays}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ziyad al-Adjam}}\n[[Category:Medieval Persian people]]\n[[Category:Persian Arabic-language poets]]\n[[Category:Persian poets]]\n", "text_old": "'''Ziy\u0101d al-A\u02bfd\u0332j\u0332am''' was an [[Arabic language|Arabic]] poet of the [[Umayyad Dynasty|Umayyad period]]. Of [[Persian people|Persian]]<ref name=\"eol\" /> origin, he was a [[mawla]] of the Amir b. al-Harith, a branch of the [[Abd al-Qays|Abd al-Kays]]. Ziy\u0101d owed his nickname, \"al-A\u02bfd\u0332j\u0332am,\" to his strong Persian accent. According to anecdotes told in the ''[[Aghani]]'', his grammar and pronunciation of spoken Arabic was not ideal.<ref name=\"eol\">{{cite book|last1=Pellat|first1=prepared by a number of leading orientalists ; edited by ... H.A.R. Gibb, J.H. Kramers, E. L\u00e9vi-Proven\u00e7al, J. Schacht, ... B. Lewis, Ch.|title=The encyclopaedia of Islam|date=1960|publisher=E.J. Brill|location=Leiden|isbn=9004127569|page=522|edition=New|quote=Of Persian origin, h